━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Check if an observations table/migration already exists.

IF it already exists:
  Read the existing columns.
  Create an ADDITIVE migration to add only missing columns.
  Never drop existing columns.
  Name the migration: add_missing_fields_to_observations_table

IF it does not exist:
  Create a fresh migration: create_observations_table

Target schema (check which columns are missing and add them):

Schema: observations table

  id                    BIGINT UNSIGNED AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY
  observation_id        VARCHAR(30) UNIQUE NOT NULL
                        -- Format: OBS-YYYY-NNNN e.g. OBS-2026-0001
                        -- Generated server-side on creation
  
  title                 VARCHAR(500) NOT NULL
  description           TEXT NOT NULL
  
  observed_date         DATE NOT NULL
  observed_time         TIME NOT NULL
  observed_day          VARCHAR(10)
                        -- Auto: Monday/Tuesday etc. stored for 
                        -- filtering convenience
  
  reported_by           VARCHAR(255) NOT NULL
                        -- Safety Officer name or user reference
  reported_by_user_id   BIGINT UNSIGNED NULL
                        REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE SET NULL
  
  team_name             VARCHAR(255) NULL
  supervisor_name       VARCHAR(255) NULL
  manager_name          VARCHAR(255) NULL
  responsible_person    VARCHAR(255) NULL
                        -- Concerned person for action
  
  category              VARCHAR(100) NULL
                        -- Unsafe Act / Unsafe Condition / 
                        -- Positive / Housekeeping / Environment /
                        -- Behavioural / Other
  
  priority              ENUM('Low','Medium','High','Critical') 
                        DEFAULT 'Medium'
  
  status                ENUM('Open','In Progress','Closed','Overdue')
                        DEFAULT 'Open'
  
  target_completion_date DATE NULL
  actual_closure_date    DATE NULL
  
  corrective_measures    TEXT NULL
  remarks               TEXT NULL
  verified_by           VARCHAR(255) NULL
  
  before_photo          VARCHAR(1000) NULL
                        -- file path / storage URL
  after_photo           VARCHAR(1000) NULL
  
  is_overdue            TINYINT(1) DEFAULT 0
                        -- 1 if past target date and not closed
                        -- updated by scheduler or on read
  
  created_by            BIGINT UNSIGNED NULL
                        REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE SET NULL
  updated_by            BIGINT UNSIGNED NULL
                        REFERENCES users(id) ON DELETE SET NULL
  
  created_at            TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
  updated_at            TIMESTAMP DEFAULT CURRENT_TIMESTAMP 
                        ON UPDATE CURRENT_TIMESTAMP
  deleted_at            TIMESTAMP NULL
                        -- soft delete

  INDEXES:
    INDEX idx_obs_status (status)
    INDEX idx_obs_date (observed_date)
    INDEX idx_obs_team (team_name)
    INDEX idx_obs_reported_by (reported_by)
    INDEX idx_obs_priority (priority)
    INDEX idx_obs_category (category)

OBSERVATION CATEGORIES (store as configurable, 
  default options):
  'Unsafe Act'
  'Unsafe Condition'  
  'Positive Observation'
  'Housekeeping'
  'Environmental'
  'Behavioural'
  'Work at Height'
  'Lifting & Rigging'
  'Near Miss'
  'Property Damage'
  'Other'

After writing the migration:
  Run: php artisan migrate
  Confirm: "Migrated successfully"

